   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GIZ - Access and Benefit Sharing Development Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Access and Benefit Sharing Program (ABS) is contributing to the implementation of the UN Convention on Biological Diversity Nagoya Protocol on international trade with genetic materials. The ABS Initiative supports African countries in the ratification process and in preparing for the associated legal, institutional and management adaptations required for implementing the Protocol. Benefits from a fair trade with genetic resource and associated tradition knowledge must according to the objectives of the ABS Program reach local communities and indigenous peoples, who are the custodians of the resources. The program is supported by several donors and has much support and engagement from private business wanting to see an end to pirating of natural resources from developing countries detrimental to responsible CSR policies. The Danish support will be administered in close consultation with the Ministry of Environment, who is responsible for matters under the Convention for Biological Diversity</narrative>
  </description>
